description: Tests mirror the src package structure for so100_pose
globs:
alwaysApply: false
---

- Place tests under `tests/so100_pose/`, mirroring paths in `src/so100_pose/`.
- For `src/so100_pose/<path>/<module>.py`, use `tests/so100_pose/<path>/test_<module>.py`.
- Prefer colocating focused tests per module over large monolithic suites.
- Pytest adds `src` to `PYTHONPATH`; avoid per-test path hacks.

Examples:
- `src/so100_pose/pose_optimization/losses.py` → `tests/so100_pose/pose_optimization/test_losses.py`
- `src/so100_pose/gradio_app/models/model.py` → `tests/so100_pose/gradio_app/models/test_model.py`
